<exercisegroup><introduction><p>Problems 71 and 72 show that multiplication by <m>i</m> results in a rotation of <m>90\degree</m>.</p></introduction>

<exercise number="71"><statement><p>Suppose that <m>z = a + bi</m> and that the real numbers <m>a</m> and
<m>b</m> are both nonzero.
<ol>
    <li><p>What is the slope of the segment in the complex plane joining the origin to <m>z</m>?</p></li>
    <li><p>What is the slope of the segment in the complex plane joining the origin to <m>zi</m>?</p></li>
    <li><p>What is the product of the slopes of the two segments from parts (a) and (b)? What can you conclude about the angle between the two segments?</p></li>
</ol></p></statement>
<answer><p><ol cols="3">
    <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{b}{a} </m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{a}{-b} </m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>-1</m>; The angle is <m>90\degree</m>.</p></li>
</ol></p></answer>
</exercise>


